In '''[[the Gambia]]''', [[Mandinka language|Mandingo]] is spoken as a first '''language''' by 38% of the population, [[Fula language|Fula]] is spoken by 21.2%, [[Wolof language|Wolof]] / [[Serer language|Serer]] by 18%, [[Jola languages|Jola]] by 4.5%. Several other languages are also spoken. [[Gambian Sign Language]] is used by the deaf.

[[English language|English]] is the main language used for official purposes and in education.

