'''Olav Vesaas''' (born 21 December 1935) is a Norwegian journalist, biographer and publisher.
He was born in [[Vinje]] to novelist [[Tarjei Vesaas]] and poet [[Halldis Moren Vesaas]], and is a brother of [[Guri Vesaas]].<ref name=allkunne>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Olav Vesaas |first=Ottar |last=Grepstad |editor-first=Ottar |editor-last=Grepstad |editor-link=Ottar Grepstad |encyclopedia=Allkunne |publisher=Nynorsk kultursentrum |location= |url= https://www.allkunne.no/framside/biografiar/v/olav-vesaas//105/1025/ |language=Norwegian|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref><ref name = dagogtid>{{cite news |title = Midtbø: -- “Fuglane” er favoritten |first=Ottar |last= Fyllingsnes |url=http://old.dagogtid.no/arkiv/1997/34/borna.html | newspaper =[[Dag og Tid]]| date=21 August 1997 |access-date = 15 August 2018 |language =Norwegian }}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Olav Vesaas |first= |last= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Bolstad | editor-first=Erik | editor-link= |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=https://snl.no/Olav_Vesaas |language=Norwegian |accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> From 1968 to 1998 he was assigned with the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]], where he mainly hosted programs on literature. From 1974 to 1990 he hosted the [[linguist]]ic radio show ''Språkrøret'', along with philologist [[Finn-Erik Vinje]].<ref name=allkunne/> From 1978 to 1980 he chaired the [[Nynorsk]] publishing house [[Det Norske Samlaget]].<ref name=allkunne/> In 2018 he was awarded {{ill|Storegutprisen|nn}}, for his lifelong contributions to literature and language.<ref name=allkunne/>
==Selected works== *''Løynde land'' (1995, biography of [[Tarjei Vesaas]]) *''A.O. Vinje – ein tankens hermann'' (2001, biography of [[Aasmund Olavsson Vinje]]) *''Å vera i livet'' (2007, biography of [[Halldis Moren Vesaas]]).
