<small>Notes:
# Some [[linguistics|linguists]] argue that [[Galician language|Galician]], spoken in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], is merely a dialect of Portuguese rather than an independent language; this would make northwestern [[Spain]] a part of the Portuguese-speaking world.
